      "message": "[Critical] Line 144: Expired pushes return before re-arming background deactivation, which can leave accounts active indefinitely in the cold-start/background case described by the comment. The new early return skips backgroundActiveSince setup, removeCallbacks, and scheduleBackgroundDeactivation(), so if an expiration push wakes the process while accounts are active, no cap/deactivation timer is installed. Keep the energy-saving behavior by skipping restore/reconnect/grace extension, but still post a deactivation check.\n```suggestion\n        if (isExpiration) {\n            backgroundHandler.post { scheduleBackgroundDeactivation() }\n            return\n        }\n```",
